# The Role of Human Activity in Climate Change: A Comprehensive Analysis

Climate change, characterized by long-term alterations in temperature, precipitation, and weather patterns, has become one of the most pressing global challenges. The question of whether human activities cause climate change has been extensively studied and debated. This report provides a detailed, evidence-based analysis of the role humans play in climate change, drawing on recent and reliable scientific literature and consensus statements.

## Scientific Consensus on Human-Caused Climate Change

The overwhelming majority of scientific studies and climate experts agree that human activities are the primary drivers of recent climate change. Multiple large-scale reviews of peer-reviewed literature have quantified this consensus:

- A comprehensive survey of nearly 90,000 climate-related scientific papers published between 2012 and 2020 found that more than **99.9%** of these studies support the conclusion that human activities are the main cause of climate change ([Lea, 2021](https://www.msn.com/en-us/news/technology/scientific-consensus-is-clear-humans-cause-climate-change-ahead-of-cop26-summit/ar-AAPL4tX)).

- Earlier studies, such as one analyzing over 12,000 abstracts from 1991 to 2012, found a 97% consensus among actively publishing climate scientists that humans are causing global warming ([Cook et al., 2013](https://lens.monash.edu/@science/2021/10/21/1383952/the-scientific-consensus-on-climate-change-gets-even-stronger)).

- Surveys of climate scientists show that consensus increases with expertise: among Earth scientists overall, agreement on human-caused warming rose from 80% in 2009 to over 91% in 2021, while among climate scientists specifically, consensus increased from 97.4% to 98.7% ([Doran et al., 2009; Cook et al., 2021](https://lens.monash.edu/@science/2021/10/21/1383952/the-scientific-consensus-on-climate-change-gets-even-stronger)).

- The Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change (IPCC) has progressively strengthened its language over decades, culminating in the 2021 report stating it is "unequivocal that human influence has warmed the atmosphere, ocean and land" ([IPCC, 2021](https://climate.nasa.gov/scientific-consensus/)).

